<div class="section">
    <h2>üìñ Project Synopsis</h2>
    <p><strong>Spectral Quest: Rainbow Craft</strong> is a narrative-driven vertical scrolling game where players embody <strong>Lirien</strong>, a Rainbow Weaver unicorn on a quest to restore the shattered Living Spectrum. Through 7 chromatic layers, players collect Harmony Shards while competing with Essence Harvester drones serving <strong>Maximum</strong> (formerly Caelum Voss), a cyborg unicorn transformed by their grandfather's cruel "purification" experiments.</p>
    
    <h3>Core Gameplay Loop:</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>7 Vertical Layers:</strong> Crimson ‚Üí Amber ‚Üí Yellow ‚Üí Green ‚Üí Blue ‚Üí Indigo ‚Üí Violet (2400px each)</li>
        <li><strong>Dual Resource System:</strong> Chromatic Essence (fuel, auto-collected) + Spectral Motes (goal, manual collection)</li>
        <li><strong>Ecological Competition:</strong> Drones harvest the same Essence to grow Binary Wrap (not traditional enemies)</li>
        <li><strong>180-Second Timer:</strong> Per layer, escalating difficulty (7 motes ‚Üí 49 motes)</li>
        <li><strong>BSV NFT Integration:</strong> Each completed layer generates a Chronicle NFT (1sat Ordinals) featuring route SVG + stats</li>
        <li><strong>Final Boss:</strong> High Cleric Voss (Maximum's grandfather) in a multi-phase battle requiring collected Memory Fragments</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Unique Selling Points:</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Queer-Centered Narrative:</strong> Non-binary protagonists, themes of identity transformation and redemption</li>
        <li><strong>Blockchain as Art:</strong> NFTs are playable souvenirs, not pay-to-win (route art + stats + lore)</li>
        <li><strong>Ethical Monetization:</strong> Free-to-play core, optional micropayments for cosmetics/fast-travel</li>
        <li><strong>Novel Tie-In:</strong> 7-book series expanding lore, QR codes linking game chapters to novel excerpts</li>
        <li><strong>Merch Ecosystem:</strong> Unicorn stuffies, enamel pins, posters (10% proceeds to QMUNITY)</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Target Audience:</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Primary:</strong> 2SLGBTQI+ gamers (18-35, 70% growth since 2020 per GLAAD)</li>
        <li><strong>Secondary:</strong> Indie game enthusiasts, blockchain art collectors, fantasy readers</li>
        <li><strong>Tertiary:</strong> Educators (game explores themes of resilience, consent, technological ethics)</li>
    </ul>
</div>

